		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-WL1375B189_01.jpg"/>
			<p>B. 189 - English Translation</p>

			<p>I am an <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-304" type="subject">refugee</term> just <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-827" type="subject">16</term> years of age, who has luckily managed for
				several months to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">escape</term> with my life from
				that hell – and by hell I mean <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> occupied by 15- to
				25-year-old <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-119" type="subject">criminals</term>.</p>
			<p>I cannot describe here in a few short lines all the dreadful and horrible things that I experienced just five months ago. Even if I
				were to speak about it for years, it would be impossible to relate everything that I suffered personally.</p>
			<p>I will try to report a little, however, of course only that which I personally felt physically or saw with my own eyes.</p>
			<p>The days after the <date when="1938-03-13">13th March 1938</date>:</p>
			<p>At this time Nazis armed with revolvers and fixed bayonets often intruded into <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">Jewish homes</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">businesses</term> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">loot</term> them.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">Jewish businesses</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-356" type="subject">daubed</term> with white or black paint and next to
				drawings which were supposed to show Jews one could read the following inscription on every <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">Jewish business</term>: <q><foreign xml:lang="de">JUD
						oder SAUJUD</foreign></q> [Jew or Jewish Pig], some time later: <q><foreign xml:lang="de">BIN SCHON IN <placeName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">DACHAU</placeName></foreign></q> [Already in
					<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>] etc. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">Jewish businesses</term> were placed under the
				management of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term> commissioners if they had
				not been <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-334" type="subject">arisiert</term></q> [Aryanised] straight
				away, which means they were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbed</term> by
				Nazis.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">Jewish lawyers</term>were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-665" type="subject">deprived</term>of the right to practise their
				profession. 15,000 Jews were already out of work in <date when="1938-04">April</date> and being fed by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-002399">Israelitisch Kultusgemeinde</term> [<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-872" type="subject">Jewish community</term>].</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">Men</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">rounded up</term> together at random on the streets or
				fetched from <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">homes</term> by the brown[-shirted]
				hordes for <q><foreign xml:lang="de">Reiben</foreign></q> [washing]. They had to wash off the labels of the old regime, at which they
				were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">laughed at</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject">mistreated</term> by the Nazis.</p>
			<p>Sometimes the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">SA</orgName> occupied <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">Jewish homes</term> in order to listen to <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Hitler's</persName> speeches on the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-850" type="subject">radio</term>.</p>
			<p>On the streets elderly Jews not infrequently were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-642" type="subject"
					>made</term> to perform military exercises or gymnastics.</p>
			<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-652" type="subject">Imprisonments</term> begin:</p>
			<p>If a Jew attempted to leave for abroad he was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject"
					>arrested</term>, because he was presumed to be a <q><foreign xml:lang="de">Fluchtgefahr</foreign></q> [escape risk].</p>
			<p>On the other hand, if a Jew had not attempted to leave, then he <q>wanted</q> to remain in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">Germany</placeName> and was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> anyway!</p>
			<p>Prominent <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> Jews mostly came into <q><foreign
						xml:lang="de"><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-620" type="subject"
					>Schutzhaft</term></foreign></q>
				<note type="gloss">protective custody</note>.</p>
			<pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-WL1375B189_02.jpg"/>
			<p>Life became insufferable and scores of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Viennese</placeName> made an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-217" type="subject">end to their lives</term> of their own free will at
				the moment of their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrest</term>, though it often
				seemed that they had been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot</term> by the Nazis
				who had forced their way into their homes. Thousands of large lorries were driven by young Nazis through the streets of <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> shouting <q><foreign xml:lang="de">Juda
					verrecke</foreign></q> [perish Judah]. Nowhere was safe for life as a Jew any more, since even a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">five-year-old</term> boy had a knife 20 cm long, with
				which he <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1159" type="subject">threatened</term>
				<q><foreign xml:lang="de">Saujuden</foreign></q> or was allowed to or should injure them.</p>
			<p>I myself attended a Realgymnasium [secondary <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject"
					>school</term>] where the majority of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject"
					>pupils</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term>. After
					<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Hitler</persName> invaded, the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">pupils</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-916" type="subject">Jewish ones</term> so severely that the Nazi director
				of our establishment felt obliged to issue the following instruction: <q><term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term><term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">pupils</term> in future will not be aggressive
					towards <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-916" type="subject">Jewish pupils</term> in the <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">school</term> building, since the fate of these
					people is being determined outside the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject"
						>school</term></q>.</p>
			<p>I would like to point out that this directive naturally had not the slightest effect on the <q><placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/2921044/federal-republic-of-germany.html">German</placeName>-<term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">Aryan</term></q>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214" type="subject">pupils</term> equipped with revolvers, knives,
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">boots</term>, brown and white <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836">shirts</term>: they continued to come to lessons in the same garb and
				clearly showed that the Nazis were there now.</p>
			<p>After a while I had to attend a <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-879" type="subject">Jewish
						school</term></q>, at which young, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-358" type="subject">National
					Socialist</term> professors were said to deliver lessons on all subjects. They did not do this, and contented themselves with
				coming to school in <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-429">SS</orgName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1091">uniform</term> and threatening the poor <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-916" type="subject">Jewish pupils</term>.</p>
			<p>Outside <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1134" type="subject">school</term> one did not have to
						<q><foreign xml:lang="de">Reiben</foreign></q> [wash] any more. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">Homes</term> were no longer occupied by Nazis who
				wanted to listen to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-850">radio</term> or <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">loot</term> valuables; no one was raided by the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> in the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">home,</term> and almost every <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> Jew was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> and dispatched to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>
				<term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496">concentration camp</term>. The period of mass <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrests</term> had begun...</p>
			<p>If someone rang at the door of a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">Jewish home</term>,
				one did not open it for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-829" type="subject">fear</term> that it would be
				the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>. One dreaded going to the telephone, and
				one dared not speak in one’s own <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">home</term>,
				because a microphone could have been installed somewhere and a rash word meant <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrest</term>.</p>
			<p>If two Jews walked together in the street then they were exposed to the danger of being <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> by the <orgName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">SA</orgName> , and if they did not give the identical answer to the
				Nazis’ question on what they had been speaking about, then they would be <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> immediately.</p>
			<p>During these months I spent more than one day unhappy, more than one night sleepless.</p>
			<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> every Jew aged over 18 years was <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-662" type="subject">threatened</term> with unfounded <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrest</term> and the SPECTRE OF <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">DACHAU</placeName>!</p>
			<p>On some days, orders came from Herr <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000070">[Josef]
					Bürckel</persName> [<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1177" type="subject">Gauleiter</term> of
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName>], and then, for example, 2,000 or another time
				again 800 Jews were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term>.</p>
			<p>Neither my father nor my uncle avoided unfounded <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject"
					>arrest</term>.</p>
			<pb n="3" facs="EHRI-ET-WL1375B189_03.jpg"/>
			<p>In the same way as I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-196" type="subject">stood</term> in front of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669" type="subject">prison</term> for endless days and nights crying
				and confused, so did many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> whose
				fathers, and many, many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>, whose husbands
				or sons had been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> without reason.</p>
			<p>Mostly all attempts for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-619">release</term> were in vain, and after two
				days the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transport</term> went to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Jews were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">rounded up</term> in the streets, from
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">homes</term> , from <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-889" type="subject">businesses</term> and coffeehouses, no longer for
						<q><foreign xml:lang="de">Reiben</foreign></q> but for <q>Freifahrt nach <placeName
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName></q> [free travel to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>], as the <q>noble</q> Nazis described
				it.</p>
			<p>There is no Jewish <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> who is not affected by this insufferable misfortune; at least
				one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term> from every <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> is in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-620" type="subject"><foreign xml:lang="de">Schutzhaft</foreign></term>
				[protective custody] and whilst he is being <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject"
					>tortured</term> and martyred in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp"
					>Dachau</placeName> or <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-43" type="camp">Buchenwald</placeName>,
				his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">relatives</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> are close to despair.</p>
			<p>People place such suffering upon people!</p>
			<p>Whilst I am writing this and no longer suffer, things are even worse for the poor Jews in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName> than at the time when I was still there. Evidence should be
				the lines written to me by a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">lady</term> who has
				also <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">escaped</term> that hell for some time, and
				what was reported to me by a friend who is already in a foreign country.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">lady</term> in question writes:</p>
			<p><q>I cannot describe to you what we have been part of, because a book would not suffice to record everything that we had to experience
					and suffer. I lived with my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">relative</term> Dr.
					N. since <date>1st November</date>. On the Thursday in question there were house searches for every Jew, and then we were all
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-652" type="subject">locked up</term>, even the <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">child</term>. The 10 mark note that my cousin had
					lent me was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">taken</term> from me though that was
					everything I possessed, and I had to sign that I had all my possessions. In <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/3247449/aachen.html">Aachen</placeName> I was stripped bare, and then a <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940">train</term> was going to <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/2800867/bruxelles-capitale.html">Brussels</placeName>, and I took this <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940">train</term>, to be able at last to get out of the hell.</q></p>
			<p>A friend reports:</p>
			<p>Firstly, I must apologise for my long silence. So much has happened since I last wrote to you that I could neither reply to any <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-843">letters</term> nor pay any visits, because the events left me not a
				minute free. We, i.e. my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term>, had to
				survive <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-652" type="subject">imprisonment</term> and a house
				search...</p>
			<p>After endless queuing and much running about we finally succeeded in obtaining a [tax certificate] and thus we have fortunately <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-203" type="subject">arrived</term> in X...</p>
			<p>You can hardly imagine what has played out in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject"
					>Germany</term> since the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-103" type="subject">assassination</term>
				of <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1118">Ambassador</term>
				<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-001144">vom Rath</persName>.</p>
			<p>That we were not <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> or <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-655" type="subject">looted</term> on that black Thursday is only
				attributable to the exemplary and honourable <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-246" type="subject"
					>behaviour</term> of our <foreign xml:lang="de">Blockleiter</foreign> [block leader].</p>
			<p>In total, roughly 2,500 male <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-827" type="subject">youths</term> of our age
				(18 years!) were sent to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-177" type="camp">Dachau</placeName>...</p>
			<pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-WL1375B189_04.jpg"/>
			<p>It is so dreadful that one cannot write about what I alone have seen.</p>
			<p>One cannot really celebrate one’s freedom when one thinks of the lot of those who are left behind in that hell!</p>
			<p>Report of a 16-year-old male <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-827" type="subject">youth</term> from
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2761369/vienna.html">Vienna</placeName>, forwarded by Frau <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_prywes_dora">Dora Prywes</persName>, <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2803138/antwerpen.html"
					>Antwerp</placeName>, c/o <persName ref="#ehri_et_hirsch_menko_max">Menko Max Hirsch</persName>.</p>

